      "content": "i see what you mean about civil rights, but it feels like you're saying the state's version of \"equality\" is the only one that matters. if the government can just decide which religious beliefs are \"valid\" and which ones are \"harmful\" enough to be overruled, aren't they basically just picking a side and forcing their own secular morality on everyone? how is that a neutral state?",
