      "content": "The government doesn't need to validate every belief to remain neutral; it only needs to ensure that no group can use their faith to oppress others. When religious exemptions are used to deny services to LGBTQ+ individuals or discriminate against minorities, the state must step in to protect the most vulnerable, because a democracy that tolerates discrimination based on identity is not truly free. This isn't about the state picking a side on theology, but rather upholding the non-negotiable principle that human dignity and equal access to society's benefits are more important than any specific religious doctrine.",
